  "riddle": "1. Seek the origins of a tennis talent who stepped into the world on what day, illuminating the calendar with her birth date? \n\n2. In the year of her first leap into the championships, which city hosted a grand event down under, noted for its celebration of the summer season?\n\n3. As you admire the location of this significant tournament, ponder: how high does the ground rise above the waves in this bustling metropolis of Australia?\n\n4. Nearby, countless facilities stand ready to care for the ailing. How many hospitals can be found in close proximity to this vibrant city?\n\n5. With the elevation noted in clue 3 and the count of nearby hospitals from clue 4, combine them to determine the absolute difference from 10 in your discoveries.\n\n6. Explore the realm where professional tennis is crafted, and calculate how many days stretch from the summer of 1975 until the spring of 2026.\n\n7. The annals of tennis history record the most outstanding player of 1977. Who claimed the title that year, marking an exceptional moment in the sport's annual accolades?\n\n8. From the champion’s name uncovered in clue 7, what is the alphabetical position of the very first letter? (Remember, A=1, B=2, and so forth.)\n\n9. Finally, with the findings of clue 3, clue 5, clue 6, and clue 8 in mind, compute the result of (10 + 10 + 18507 + 22) modulo 10. Your answer shall reveal a single digit, ranging between 0 and 9.",
